<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1497,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1883,1909]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from Latin ‘multiciliata’ meaning hairy, referring to the full covering of body hair. Gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1497,2026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
